    <h3>Multi-Stage Decision Workflow (LangGraph)</h3>
    <p>
        The system is implemented as a deterministic state machine using LangGraph. Each decision request flows through
        explicit
        nodes: intake normalization, authoritative RAG retrieval, historical memory lookup, independent analysis,
        structured planning,
        decision synthesis, confidence modeling, and report generation. Each node owns specific state fields and
        produces a
        semantically complete state when executed. This architecture avoids hidden coupling and ensures traceability
        across the
        entire reasoning pipeline.
    </p>

    <img src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/04d08503-eda9-4ef3-a3a8-c5580f024c5d"
        class="portfolio-details__img" alt="RAG Context and Evidence" />

    <h3>Authoritative RAG & Context Governance</h3>
    <p>
        Organizational documents can be uploaded and treated as authoritative constraints. Documents are embedded and
        stored in
        ChromaDB, retrieved via semantic similarity, and injected into the decision context. The system explicitly
        distinguishes
        between authoritative context (organizational truth) and historical decisions (precedent evidence). This reduces
        hallucinations
        and enforces alignment with real-world business constraints.
    </p>

    <img src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/bba00816-addb-48c9-b159-703455f4a9d2"
        class="portfolio-details__img" alt="Historical Decisions" />

    <h3>Historical Decision Intelligence</h3>
    <p>
        The system maintains long-term semantic memory of past decisions. Similarity-based retrieval identifies related
        historical
        cases and computes an influence factor that adjusts final confidence. This allows the engine to quantify
        precedent impact
        rather than merely referencing it, moving toward AI governance rather than simple generation.
    </p>

    <img src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/dbfe0f52-ffcd-4235-8a84-47c140a0e62e"
        class="portfolio-details__img" alt="Decision Output" />

    <h3>Deterministic Confidence Modeling</h3>
    <p>
        Confidence is not taken from the LLM. Instead, the system computes base confidence, applies historical influence
        adjustments,
        and derives a final deterministic score with explicit label mapping. Low-confidence outcomes can trigger retries
        or fallback
        handling. Confidence drift tracking allows monitoring changes over time, separating generative output from
        evaluation metrics.
    </p>

    <img src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/56dfc6e6-4517-4c03-85cf-feb5da4a454b"
        class="portfolio-details__img" alt="Session Report" />

    <h3>Audit-Ready Session Reporting</h3>
    <p>
        Every session generates a structured report including decision outcome, reasoning, contextual evidence,
        historical influence,
        and full confidence breakdown. Reports are exportable in HTML, PDF, and DOCX formats, supporting governance
        workflows and
        executive-level documentation requirements.
    </p>

    <img src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/11398f77-2d9a-43c8-b1f8-2ceb210cc9c4"
        class="portfolio-details__img" alt="System Messages and Logs" />

    <h3>Cost Governance & Deployment Awareness</h3>
    <p>
        A dedicated Token Budget Manager enforces session-level and daily limits to control cloud costs in the public
        Hugging Face
        deployment. Quota exhaustion leads to explicit refusal rather than uncontrolled LLM calls. Logging is performed
        at node level
        via a decorator-based system, ensuring traceable execution and easier debugging in production-like environments.
    </p>

